this implementation can be improved in terms of hot path isolation:

string is not null and longer than zero (hot)
string is null or empty (less frequent - cold)

hot path might look like:
if (str != null) {
    for (int i = 0, n=str.length(); i < n; i++) {
                sink.put(toLowerCase(str.charAt(i)));
    }
}
note that is str.length() is not cached into local variable, java will be calling length() method for every iteration

